This form expects a POST endpoint like this on the backend:
POST /api/transactions
Body: {
  type: "income" | "expense",
  category: "Food",
  amount: 1000,
  description: "Lunch",
  date: "2025-06-15"
}


Ensure this route exists:
GET /api/transactions
Response format:
[
  {
    "type": "income",
    "category": "Salary",
    "amount": 20000,
    "description": "May Salary",
    "date": "2025-06-01"
  },
  ...
]


You need a POST route:
POST /api/transactions/bulk

{
  "transactions": [
    {
      "date": "2025-06-01",
      "type": "expense",
      "category": "Food",
      "amount": 300,
      "description": "Lunch"
    },
    ...
  ]
}

Backend Requirements
Routes needed on the backend:

POST /auth/register

POST /auth/login

POST /auth/logout

GET /auth/me (return current user from session or token)


Schema Example (in your database)
Goal {
  id
  userId
  title: string
  targetAmount: number
  savedAmount: number
  deadline: date
}


Endpoints:
GET /goals → fetch all user's goals

POST /goals → create a new goal

PATCH /goals/:id → update savedAmount
{
  "_id": "abc123",
  "title": "Emergency Fund",
  "targetAmount": 50000,
  "savedAmount": 10000,
  "deadline": "2025-12-31"
}
